HEADWORD: Vestured
<hw>Ves"tured</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Covered with vesture
or garments; clothed; enveloped.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>We be <qex>vestured</qex> with poor cloth.</q> <rj><qau>Ld.
Berners.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Vesuvian</ent>⟦br⟧
